description:
Ancient Greek ἀ- (a-, “without”) + γνάθος (gnáthos, “jaw”)  +‎ -ous.
From a- +‎ -gnathous.

examples: The Onchidiidæ are described as agnathous, but I am confident of having observed the jaw figured.

entries.meaning: (pathology) Afflicted by or characteristic of agnathia.
examples: In all the neonates examined from the partially agnathous strain, there was no obvious agenesia of the lower mandible.
